div.p: RHINFELD a ſmall but ſtrong town of Germany, in tbe circle of Suabia, and the beſt oſ the four foreſt-towns belonging to the houſe of Auſtria. It has been often taken and retaken in the German wars ; and is ſeated on tbe Rhine, over which there is a handfome bridge. E. Long. 7. 53· N. Lat. 47. 40.
